The Ten Commandments of Project Disc
1. Music Comes First

Every design decision should improve the listening experience.

2. Durability Over Thinness

A strong device is better than a fragile one.

3. Repair Before Replace

If something breaks, it should be fixable.

4. Modularity Matters

Components should be replaceable and reusable whenever practical.

5. Simplicity Wins

The simplest reliable solution is usually the best one.

6. Every Part Has a Purpose

Avoid unnecessary hardware, software, and visual clutter.

7. Document Everything

If it exists, document it.

If it changes, update the documentation.

8. Respect the User's Time

Fast boot.

Responsive controls.

Clear navigation.

Easy repairs.

Straightforward updates.

9. Build for the Long Term

Assume the device will still be used five to ten years from now.

10. Build Something You're Proud to Carry

If we wouldn't use it every day, it doesn't belong in Project Disc.

11. Repairability by Design

Repairability shall be considered during the initial design of every component rather than added as an afterthought.
